node.code:
Many years ago, near the inception of the [Voting/Experience System], there was a time when there were
no minimum writeups required to gain levels.  Noders rose to terrific height on XP alone, using quests
and votes to skyrocket to stratospheric levels.
<p>When minimum writeups was finally implemented, some noders dropped levels.  Some were given the
option to get their levels back, if they wanted.
<p>These are those who chose to take back their old level:
<p>[%
  my $V = getVars(getNode('level weenies', 'setting'));
  my $str;
  my @names = keys %$V;
 @names = reverse(sort {$$V{$a} <=> $$V{$b}} @names);

  foreach (@names) {
    $str.="<li>[$_] was granted $$V{$_}\n";
 }
$str;
%]
<p>Of course, it's going to be that much harder to gain their <i>next</i> level, since they still have
to fill its minimum writeup requirement...
